gloss.term:
Practices of the bodhisattva path: generosity (Tib. sbyin pa; Skt. dāna), discipline (Tib. tshul khrims; Skt.
                                                                        śīla), patience (Tib. bzod pa; Skt.
                                                                        kṣānti), diligence (Tib. brtson ’grus;
                                                                Skt. vīrya), concentration (Tib. bsam gtan;
                                                                Skt. dhyāna), and wisdom (Tib. shes rab; Skt.
                                                                        prajñā).
